Traders of various markets in Benue State have flouted the directives of the Benue State government to shutdown markets and stay indoor for 14 days. Our correspondent observed that  market managers and security are making brisk business from traders by allowing them to pay from N200 and above, depending on what they are selling to enable them bring out their goods on the main streets that passes in front of the said markets to sell. Governor Samuel Ortom who went round some major markets in Makurdi metropolis to observe the level of compliance expressed shock that despite campaigns and awareness creation by the state government on the dangers of COVID-19 and ways of preventing its outbreak in the state, all appeals fell on deaf ears. It was also observed during the tour that aside Modern Market all other markets like Wurukum, High Level and Wadata markets did not comply with the directives as the traders were seen  transacting their normal businesses. In an interview with some of the traders in North Bank Markets the traders said that selling their wares in  the market is the only source of feeding their families and if they don’t  come out to sell it their families will have to go hungry. They called on the government of President Muhammadu  Buhari to ensure that the palletives being given to citizens in other states also reached Benue to enable some of them who are bread winners of their families put food on the table as they comply with the directives. Ortom who expressed disappointment with the attitude of the traders said as from today the state government will commence the fumigation of all the major markets in Makurdi as recommended by the World Health Organisation (WHO) warning that during the fumigation exercise it would not allow traders come around the markets. “Today we are begging you to obey   the directive but as from Thursday the security agencies will be enforcing this directives as it is done in other states of the federation and anyone who flout the directives will have his or herself to blame, so we need your cooperation in  to achieve our desired target”, he said.